<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26267a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26267a">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26267a"> 267(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> during pleasure</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Patricians]</font>&mdash;The client became a dependent member of his patron&apos;s clan&mdash;not <i>gentilis</i> but <i>gentilicius</i>. His patron had to provide him with what was necessary for his sustenance and that of his family; and, as ownership or possession of lands increased in extent, it was probably not unusual for the patron or his <i>gens</i> to give him <mark>during pleasure</mark> a plot of land to cultivate for himself. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 527</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
